FBIS4-779 "drafr073_c_94022" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Lebowa State Officials Occupy TEC Offices Lebowa State Officials Occupy TEC Offices MB1504070294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 15 Apr 94 MB1504070294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] A group of about 70 Lebowa state officials have occupied the officers of the Transitional Executive Council [TEC] in Pretoria. A spokesman for the Health and Education Workers' Union, NEHAWU, said that the group would stay there until the TEC management committee had addressed their grievances. The group say the situation in Lebowa has deteriorated since Minister of Regional and Land Affairs Mr. Andre Fourie took over the administration duties of the territory. They've asked for Mr. Fourie to be replaced by a neutral administrator and for their promotions to come into affect immediately.
